<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-transistor-introduction" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Introduction to transistors</title>

    <p>
        There are two types of BJTs, the npn transistor and the pnp transistor, pictured in <xref ref="fig-transistor-BJT-types"/>.
    </p>
    <figure xml:id="fig-transistor-BJT-types">
        <caption></caption>
        <sidebyside widths="45% 45%" valign="bottom">
            <figure xml:id="fig-transistor-BJT-types-npn">
                <caption>npn transistor.</caption>
                <image>
                    <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="fig-transistor-npn-block">
                        <xi:include href="./prefigure/fig-transistor-npn-block.xml" />
                    </prefigure>
                </image>
            </figure>
            <figure xml:id="fig-transistor-BJT-types-pnp">
                <caption>pnp transistor.</caption>
                <image>
                    <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org" label="fig-transistor-pnp-block">
                        <xi:include href="./prefigure/fig-transistor-pnp-block.xml" />
                    </prefigure>
                </image>
            </figure>
        </sidebyside>
    </figure>

</section>